 transfer, we might move one that still cannot be processed while another that could is kept pending.\r\n\r\nSince we trigger `process_pending_handles()` from various changes, the stalled pending will eventually make it to the processing queue, but this is not optimal.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/18056/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/18056/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}},"event":"cross-referenced"},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/comments/3126411374","html_url":"https://github.com/curl/curl/issues/18017#issuecomment-3126411374","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/curl/curl/issues/18017","id":3126411374,"node_id":"IC_kwDOAAiu0c66WUBu","user":{"login":"icing","id":15102,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE1MTAy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/15102?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing","html_url":"https://github.com/icing","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/icing/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2025-07-28T09:43:27Z","updated_at":"2025-07-28T09:43:27Z","body":"I propose #18056 to address this, restoring the 8.13.0 behaviour in regard to pending handles. It would be great if you could verify that PR in your